---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Disclaimer"
  description="Important legal disclaimers regarding the educational content on PepCodex. Not medical advice."
>
  <article class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-4 py-16 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <header class="mb-12 relative">
      <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-br from-amber-500/10 via-transparent to-transparent rounded-2xl -z-10"></div>
      <div class="p-6">
        <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight text-white">Disclaimer</h1>
        <p class="mt-4 text-xl text-white/80">
          Important information about the content on PepCodex.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-white/60">Last updated: January 2026</p>
      </div>
    </header>

    <div class="prose prose-invert prose-lg max-w-none">
      <!-- General Disclaimer -->
      <section id="general-disclaimer">
        <h2>General Disclaimer</h2>
        <p>
          The information provided on PepCodex ("the Website") is for <strong>educational and research
          purposes only</strong>. The content is intended to provide general information about peptide
          research based on published scientific literature.
        </p>
        <p>
          While we strive to provide accurate and up-to-date information, PepCodex makes no representations
          or warranties of any kind, express or implied, about the completeness, accuracy, reliability,
          suitability, or availability of the information, products, services, or related graphics
          contained on the Website for any purpose.
        </p>
        <p>
          Any reliance you place on such information is therefore strictly at your own risk. In no event
          will PepCodex be liable for any loss or damage including without limitation, indirect or
          consequential loss or damage, or any loss or damage whatsoever arising from loss of data or
          profits arising out of, or in connection with, the use of this Website.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Medical Disclaimer -->
      <section id="medical-disclaimer" class="mt-12">
        <h2>Medical Disclaimer</h2>

        <div class="not-prose my-8 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-500/10 p-6 backdrop-blur-sm">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-amber-400 flex-shrink-0 mt-1" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
              <path d="m21.73 18-8-14a2 2 0 0 0-3.48 0l-8 14A2 2 0 0 0 4 21h16a2 2 0 0 0 1.73-3Z"/>
              <path d="M12 9v4"/>
              <path d="M12 17h.01"/>
            </svg>
            <div>
              <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-300 mb-2">This Is Not Medical Advice</h3>
              <p class="text-white/80">
                The content on PepCodex does not constitute medical advice, diagnosis, or treatment.
                Always seek the advice of your physician or other qualified healthcare provider with
                any questions you may have regarding a medical condition.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h3>No Doctor-Patient Relationship</h3>
        <p>
          Use of PepCodex does not create a doctor-patient, therapist-patient, or other healthcare
          professional relationship between you and PepCodex, its owners, contributors, or any other
          party. The information provided on this Website should not be used as a substitute for
          professional medical advice, diagnosis, or treatment.
        </p>

        <h3>Consult Healthcare Professionals</h3>
        <p>
          Before making any decisions about your health based on information found on this Website,
          you should:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Consult with a qualified healthcare professional</li>
          <li>Inform your healthcare provider of all medications and supplements you are taking</li>
          <li>Discuss the potential risks and benefits of any treatment option</li>
          <li>Never disregard professional medical advice because of something you have read on this Website</li>
          <li>Never delay seeking medical advice because of something you have read on this Website</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>No Diagnosis or Treatment</h3>
        <p>
          PepCodex does not diagnose, treat, cure, or prevent any disease or health condition. The
          content is not intended to be a substitute for professional medical advice. If you think
          you may have a medical emergency, call your doctor or emergency services immediately.
        </p>

        <h3>Individual Results May Vary</h3>
        <p>
          The information presented on this Website describes research findings and scientific
          literature. Individual responses to any substance can vary significantly based on genetics,
          health status, other medications, and numerous other factors. Research results may not
          translate directly to individual outcomes.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Research Information Disclaimer -->
      <section id="research-disclaimer" class="mt-12">
        <h2>Research Information Disclaimer</h2>
        <p>
          The peptide research information presented on PepCodex is derived exclusively from:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Peer-reviewed scientific journals</li>
          <li>Clinical trial registries (ClinicalTrials.gov, EU Clinical Trials Register, etc.)</li>
          <li>Regulatory agency documents (FDA, EMA, MHRA, etc.)</li>
          <li>Published systematic reviews and meta-analyses</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          While we make every effort to accurately represent the findings of published research,
          scientific understanding evolves over time. New research may contradict or modify
          previously published findings. We recommend consulting the original sources and staying
          informed about the latest research developments.
        </p>

        <h3>Preclinical vs. Clinical Research</h3>
        <p>
          We clearly distinguish between preclinical (animal/in vitro) research and human clinical
          trials. Results from preclinical studies may not translate to humans. Where human data
          is limited or absent, we clearly indicate this limitation.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- User Responsibility -->
      <section id="user-responsibility" class="mt-12">
        <h2>User Responsibility</h2>
        <p>
          By using PepCodex, you acknowledge and agree that:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>You assume all responsibility</strong> for how you use the information provided on this Website
          </li>
          <li>
            You will <strong>not use this information to self-diagnose</strong> or self-treat any health condition
          </li>
          <li>
            You will <strong>consult appropriate healthcare professionals</strong> before making any health-related decisions
          </li>
          <li>
            You understand that this Website is for <strong>educational purposes only</strong>
          </li>
          <li>
            You will comply with all applicable laws and regulations in your jurisdiction
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <!-- No Endorsement -->
      <section id="no-endorsement" class="mt-12">
        <h2>No Endorsement</h2>
        <p>
          PepCodex does not endorse, recommend, or advocate for the use of any specific peptide,
          supplement, medication, or treatment. The presence of information about any substance on
          this Website should not be interpreted as an endorsement or recommendation for its use.
        </p>
        <p>
          We do not provide:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Dosing recommendations or protocols</li>
          <li>Sourcing information or purchasing guidance</li>
          <li>Recommendations for or against any specific product or supplier</li>
          <li>Medical advice for specific health conditions</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <!-- External Links -->
      <section id="external-links" class="mt-12">
        <h2>External Links</h2>
        <p>
          This Website may contain links to external websites, including scientific journals,
          clinical trial registries, and regulatory agencies. These links are provided for
          convenience and informational purposes only. PepCodex does not control and is not
          responsible for the content, privacy policies, or practices of any third-party websites.
        </p>
        <p>
          The inclusion of any link does not imply endorsement by PepCodex of the linked site
          or any association with its operators.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Changes to Disclaimer -->
      <section id="changes" class="mt-12">
        <h2>Changes to This Disclaimer</h2>
        <p>
          PepCodex reserves the right to update or modify this Disclaimer at any time without
          prior notice. Your continued use of the Website after any changes indicates your
          acceptance of the modified Disclaimer.
        </p>
        <p>
          We encourage you to review this page periodically to stay informed of any updates.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Contact -->
      <section id="contact" class="mt-12">
        <h2>Contact Us</h2>
        <p>
          If you have questions about this Disclaimer, please contact us at:
        </p>
        <p>
          Email: <a href="mailto:legal@pepcodex.com">legal@pepcodex.com</a>
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Related Pages -->
      <section id="related" class="mt-12 pt-8 border-t border-white/10">
        <h2>Related Legal Pages</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><a href="/terms">Terms of Service</a></li>
          <li><a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a></li>
          <li><a href="/fda-notice">FDA Notice</a></li>
          <li><a href="/cookie-policy">Cookie Policy</a></li>
        </ul>
      </section>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
